column432:
How can we get x on the left side and the constants on the right?


Divide both sides by the coefficient of the variable. That is, divide both sides by -1.

You have only a variable term on the right: -x. Also, you have only a constant on the left: -1. You can get the variable by itself by dividing both sides by the coefficient of the variable.
